Any sort of comparison will contribute 1 to the count of comparisons.

What is the worst case to search an element from an Array?
ANSWER:  The worst case for this algorithm will be if the element we are searching for is the last element in the Array.

What is a tree in Data Structures?
ANSWER:  A Tree is a non-linear Data Structures where data objects are organized in terms of hierarchical relationships.

What is graph in Data Structures?
ANSWER:  A graph is a Data Structures that has two types of elements, vertices and edges.
What is the difference between the HashTable and HashMap?
ANSWER:  Hashtable is synchronized, whereas HashMap is not. This makes HashMap better for non-threaded applications, as unsynchronized Objects typically perform better than synchronized ones. ... HashMap allows one null key and any number of null values.

